parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the daytime running lights can reduce the vehicle's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The daytime running lights do not turn on
flicker
or fail to operate correctly
making the vehicle harder to see by other drivers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the daytime running lights under the recall can lead to continued safety risks and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are unable to get their daytime running lights repaired due to a lack of parts
despite repeated attempts to schedule repairs
and are not provided with a clear timeline for when the parts will become available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
